import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x="state", data=data, order=data['state'].value_counts().index)
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Number of Zip Codes')
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate(format(p.get_height(), '.0f'), (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), ha = 'center', va = 'center', xytext = (0, 10), textcoords = 'offset points')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different states?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_counts = data['city'].value_counts()
    top_cities = city_counts[:10]
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x=top_cities.index, y=top_cities.values, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='City', ylabel='Number of Zip Codes')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the most common city in the dataset?')
    plt.axhline(y=top_cities.iloc[0], color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Most common city: {top_cities.index[0]} ({top_cities.iloc[0]:,.2f})')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(16, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='county', data=data, order=data['county'].value_counts().index)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90, ha="right")
    ax.set_xlabel('County')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different counties?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.spatial.distance import pdist, squareform

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    dist_matrix = squareform(pdist(data[['latitude', 'longitude']], metric='euclidean'))
    sns.histplot(dist_matrix.flatten(), kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=dist_matrix.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {dist_matrix.mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(x=dist_matrix.min(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Min: {dist_matrix.min():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(x=dist_matrix.max(), color='purple', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {dist_matrix.max():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Distance between zip codes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
